msgctxt "sn27.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 27 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 27 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn27.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Kilesavagga "
msgstr "1. Corruptions "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn27.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Cakkhusutta "
msgstr "1. The Eye "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.232, sc1
msgctxt "sn27.1:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn27.1:1.2"
msgid "“Yo, bhikkhave, cakkhusmiṃ chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, desire and greed for the eye, "

msgctxt "sn27.1:1.3"
msgid "Yo sotasmiṃ chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso. "
msgstr "ear, "

msgctxt "sn27.1:1.4"
msgid "Yo ghānasmiṃ chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso. "
msgstr "nose, "

msgctxt "sn27.1:1.5"
msgid "Yo jivhāya chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso. "
msgstr "tongue, "

msgctxt "sn27.1:1.6"
msgid "Yo kāyasmiṃ chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso. "
msgstr "body, "

msgctxt "sn27.1:1.7"
msgid "Yo manasmiṃ chandarāgo, cittasseso upakkileso. "
msgstr "or mind is a corruption of the mind. "

msgctxt "sn27.1:1.8"
msgid "Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno imesu chasu ṭhānesu cetaso upakkileso pahīno hoti, nekkhammaninnañcassa cittaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "When a mendicant has given up mental corruption in these six cases, their mind inclines to renunciation. "

# NOTE: BB notes the difficulty with khayati, but doesn’t explain how he gets from “seems “to” becomes”. The root is, however, khā, i.e. to speak, declare, and i take it as equivalent to pannayati. regarding kammaniya, see the similar passage at AN 5.68, etc, where bhabba is used. Kammaniya must have a similar sense.
msgctxt "sn27.1:1.9"
msgid "Nekkhammaparibhāvitaṃ cittaṃ kammaniyaṃ khāyati, abhiññā sacchikaraṇīyesu dhammesū”ti. "
msgstr "A mind imbued with renunciation is declared to be capable of directly knowing anything that can be realized.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn27.1:1.10"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

